What are the different physical factors affecting a material's electrical conductivity? Can you provide an example of a material with high and low conductivity? 
Now, let's put your knowledge to the test. Here is some JSON data with conductivity, density, and melting point values of different materials. Based on the given data, which material has the highest conductivity? 
JSON Data:
{
  "materials": [
    {
      "name": "Aluminum",
      "conductivity": {
        "units": "MS/m",
        "value": 37.7
      },
      "density": {
        "units": "kg/m³",
        "value": 2.70E+3
      },
      "melting_point": {
        "units": "K",
        "value": 933
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Gold",
      "conductivity": {
        "units": "MS/m",
        "value": 44.0
      },
      "density": {
        "units": "kg/m³",
        "value": 19.32E+3
      },
      "melting_point": {
        "units": "K",
        "value": 1.337E+3
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Silicon",
      "conductivity": {
        "units": "MS/m",
        "value": 0.001
      },
      "density": {
        "units": "kg/m³",
        "value": 2.33E+3
      },
      "melting_point": {
        "units": "K",
        "value": 1.687E+3
      }
    }
  ]
}
